title: Pet Semetary  [Dramatisation] - Stephen King
description:
Pet Semetary  
                 [Dramatisation] - Stephen King


Renowned for its superior productions, BBC radio may have outdone itself by adapting Stephen King&#039;s Pet Sematary to audio. A clamorous cacophony of talking, whining, whistling, and howling, Pet Sematary is a quick, entertaining earful for those who don&#039;t have other auditory distractions to contend with, such as a car full of talking whining, whistling, howling children. However, the melodramatic prose marries well with the acting; such is the case when one reader--whose voice bears an uncanny resemblance to Kramer&#039;s from Seinfeld--tells another about the effects of the Pet Sematary: "Heroin makes junkies feel good when they put it in their arms, but all the time it&#039;s poisoning their mind and body--this place can be like that and don&#039;t you ever forget it!"
